        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We request the lowest possible spectral resolution because the line is very wide in the observed frame.  This also maximizes the continuum sensitivity. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We want ~1" resolution to ensure robust detection of the source, constrain its size, and detect any extended gas around the source.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Based on Capak et al. 2005, we expect the line to have a sigma of ~120Km/s in the rest frame, which is ~0.15Ghz in the observed frame.  This is technically not the line width, but is the correct width to use for the sensitivity calcualtion based on prior observations.</prj:justificationText>
